The MHD Wednesday in Prague will accompany you for the first time also with an electronic card
Wednesday, October 1, 2008 will be written in the history of the Prague Transport Company as the date when the first passengers who will have an electronic card in their pockets instead of the paper ticket will board the metro, tram and bus.
At the moment about one hundred thousand people who own their Opencard can get it.
