In addition to this, the "issuers" ruined other invoices, in the case of a company they indicated as activity carried out the transport of goods by road, as is known from the procedure of the Prosecutor, activity that was not carried out by the company originally founded for investment advice.
In addition for formal defects - due to non-compliant invoice format, false stamp - it was found that the invoices issued in favour of Együtt to Harmadik Évezredért Alapítvány, of XXI. Századi Kulturális Egyesület and Biztos Pont are false.
The same happened in the case of Ravenna Bt. or the Kunfehértó Sports Field, whose representatives denied that they had issued the invoices in question.
The counterfeiters did not even pay attention to the fact that the HIB Kft. of Nyíregyháza was in liquidation when (2001) a group of Fiatal Városért Egyesület ate there, which is why, according to our information, the liquidator of the company denied that he had issued that invoice.
They consciously issued invoices.
