Industry prices continue to rise
The prices of domestic industrial sales in August 2008 increased by 0.1% compared to the previous month, by 12.9% compared to August 2007 - informs the Hungarian Central Institute of Statistics.
The prices of export sales of the industry compared to July 2008 were higher by 1.1%, compared to the previous year they decreased by 3.9%
As a result of the change in domestic and export prices, industrial production costs were 0.7% higher than the previous month and 3.2% higher than a year ago.
The prices of domestic industrial sales compared to the previous month increased only by 0.1%.
The prices of domestic sales of the processing sector also rose to a minimum extent, 0.1%, compared to July.
The biggest price increase in August 2008 occurred in the leather and shoe processing sector (2.8%), especially bags and belts with 4.6% and shoe production with a 2.5% monthly increase.
The high price level of plastics and chemical raw materials caused a significant monthly increase (1.6%) in the chemicals and products sector.
A decrease in prices occurred in the oil processing sector (1.4%), in the production of electrical tools and machinery (0.9%) and to a minimum extent in wood processing (0.1%)
The prices of paper production, publishing and printing have not changed.
In the other sectors of the processing industry there was a price increase of between 0.2 and 0.9%.
In the electricity, gas, steam and water supply sector, prices rose in August by 0.3% in domestic industrial sales, primarily as a result of the dominant effect of the gas price increase effected by the authorities since 1 July.
Compared in 12 months, considering the domestic sales of the processing industry sectors, the largest increases were in the petroleum processing sector (32.4%).
In the manufacture of metal products, prices rose by 13.2%, compared with 11% in the food, beverage and tobacco sectors, which accounted for a significant share.
Prices fell in the textile sector (2.5%) and in the production of electrical instruments and machinery (0.3%).
In the other sectors of the processing industry, the rate of price increase varied from 0.6% to 9.1%.
In total, in the processing industry, prices rose by 10.2% in the past year.
Prices in the electricity, gas, steam and water supply sector exceeded last year's prices by 18.7%.
In domestic sales among the target groups of the sectors, the largest increase in monthly prices occurred in August in the sectors that produce investment goods (0.7%).
In the consumer goods sectors, prices increased by 0.3%, in the energy and subsequent use sectors, prices did not change compared to the previous month.
In August 2008, compared to the same month last year, the largest price increase was observed in the energy sector and subsequent use (16.8%).
In the consumer goods sectors the increase was 6.8%, for investment goods a decrease of 1.4% was measured.
The prices of industrial export sales calculated in guilders increased in August by 1.1% compared to the previous month, compared to 12 months, they decreased by 3.9%.
The Hungarian forint weakened against the euro by 1.7%, against the dollar by 7.1%, compared to August 2007 it strengthened by 7.5% against the euro and 15.9% against the dollar.
