Open Office, here is the third edition of the package"anti-Microsoft»
It is the day of the release of OpenOffice.org 3.0, the open source suite of personal productivity that aims to reach more and more users, from the home to the office, from professionals to public administration, as a free alternative to the best known Microsoft Office.
After almost a year of work by volunteer developers, behind whom SUN Microsystem watches, the new Open Office shows itself to the general public with several novelties: to the welcome screen and to the interface revised and made less spartan, are added other more substantial as the native compatibility for the operating system Apple Mac OS X and the support for the new version ODF (Open Document Format) 1.2.
Also pay attention to the interoperability with the Office 2007 suite, Open Office is able to open documents with the new Microsoft extension (.docx, .xlsx, .pptx).
Interesting some specific features of some modules such as the one that allows you to reduce the size of PowerPoint presentations, useful for example to send them by email, or the ability to import PDF files into the graphics processing module, preserving the original appearance of the page.
Also on this front you can create "hybrid PDF" documents, which combine the graphics typical of the format of Adobe with the elements of a spreadsheet or a word processor.
Collaboration is an element that has received several improvements within the applications: in the spreadsheet you can intervene with several hands between different users, avoiding conflicts on changes, in the text processor, each collaborator is assigned a color in the comments for better recognition during revision.
Some companies are also working to bring some OpenOffice features to the Web (on the cloud), and in the coming weeks they should release the final result.
The Italian version can be downloaded at http://en.openoffice.org/download/3.0.0/download300.html and has been added to the English version that was on the mirrors since Friday.
In addition to Windows and Mac OS, as usual the suite is also available for the Linux operating system.
On request, the installation CD can also be sent home or at work.
And if the theme of free can be a drag for diffusion in homes, it is precisely in the business sector that Open Office the suite tries the big bet, already being able to count on several projects carried out in the public administration and in schools.
And there are also realities that offer a training, consulting and assistance service ideal for small and medium-sized companies, which could open business prospects.
Open Office consists of five main modules: Writer, for the corresponding videowriting of Word; Calc, is the spreadsheet that aims to replace Excel; Impress, for Powerpoint emulo presentations; Dbase, as in the case of the most famous Access is the program that allows you to work on databases; Draw, is finally the graphical module.
The objective for 2008 is to reach 5 million downloads, and considering that to date we are at almost 3,600,000, with the release of the new version it is likely that we can also exceed the expected figure.
